The doctrines of Pytha— goras are supposed to have been in part de- rived from the Egyptians whose objection to eating leeks and onions is mentioned by several ancient authors, Plutarch, followed by Gellius (xx. 8), gives as the reason that they grow at the waning of the moon, and wither when she waxcs. Gellius speaks of this fancy as confined to the :nhabitants of Pelusium in the Delta.
